                        <par_12
                            jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                            sling:resourceType="wcm/foundation/components/parsys">
                            <container4
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <title2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545824678,1651545825694]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-10-07T10:17:38.872-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="Making time count for patients "
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h2"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-10-07T10:18:04.611-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>A single doctor’s visit can change the future for someone who’s been diagnosed with a serious illness, whether it be cancer, an autoimmune disease or a neurological disorder.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>For the patients receiving this news, their lives may never be the same – and the concept of time becomes more precious.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>AbbVie strives to make time count for these patients, knowing that the less time it takes to develop and deliver new treatments, the more time they can spend with the people they love.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“Creating more time for patients is what motivates and drives our teams at AbbVie,” says Nicholas Donoghoe, EVP and Chief Business &amp;amp; Strategy Officer, AbbVie. “We are laser focused on identifying efficiencies that speed up development, with the goal of going twice as fast to deliver transformational new medicines to patients.”&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <separator
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756423318]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-09-13T12:27:39.956-04:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-09-13T12:27:39.956-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <title2_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545824678,1651545825694]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-10-07T10:18:26.937-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="Accelerating the process from lab to patient"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h2"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-09-13T12:07:24.797-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>Historically, it takes 10-15 years to bring a medicine from discovery through clinical development (including clinical trial research programs that evaluate the safety and efficacy of a treatment; these data inform the application to regulatory authorities, such as the U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) for approval), and then to patients. AbbVie has set an ambitious goal to accelerate the clinical development process to help deliver medicines in half the time.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4>
                            <container
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545835982]"
                                jcr:created="{Date}2025-10-07T10:24:27.600-04:00"
                                jcr:createdBy="VALENSX5"
                                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-10-07T10:24:27.600-04:00"
                                jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <image
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2025-10-07T10:24:33.198-04:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-10-09T14:03:37.339-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/image/v2/image"
                                    altValueFromDAM="true"
                                    displayPopupTitle="true"
                                    dmPresetType="imagePreset"
                                    fileReference="/content/dam/abbvie-com2/images/stories/pipeline-acceleration/pipeline-acceleration-in-story-graphic-updated.svg"
                                    isDecorative="false"
                                    openInNewWindow="false"
                                    titleValueFromDAM="true"/>
                            </container>
                            <container4_copy
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <text2_copy_1999141463
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-10-07T10:18:56.557-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>Here are five ways the company is driving efficiency across the clinical development process:&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <separator_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756423318]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-09-13T12:27:39.956-04:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-09-13T12:27:39.956-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <title2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545824678,1651545825668]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-10-07T10:19:12.840-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="1. Delivering drug supply for clinical testing sooner"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h5"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-10-07T10:19:32.204-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>Before a clinical trial can begin, clinical trial sites need a supply of drugs to administer to trial participants. The preclinical development of drugs can be complex, particularly for novel medicines called biologics, such as monoclonal antibodies that are derived from clones of a single origin cell.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“Our goal is to bring novel assets through discovery, into development and to our patients as quickly as possible,” said Calum Park, Ph.D., vice president, product development, science and technology, AbbVie. “The more we can accelerate these timelines, the faster we can begin the clinical trial process to evaluate the safety and efficacy of the medicine.”&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>In the example of monoclonal antibody development, the standard practice used to be—and in many cases still is—that laboratories manually isolate and screen for the single origin cell, a process that could take two to three months to complete. AbbVie is accelerating that process with cutting-edge technology that uses light to move individual cells, enabling rapid isolation and screening of a single cell in about one week. This technology, along with increased manufacturing capacity and processing improvements, has allowed AbbVie to deliver monoclonal antibodies for clinical trials one year faster.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <separator_copy_389659192
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756423318]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-09-13T12:27:39.956-04:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-09-13T12:27:39.956-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <title2_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545824678,1651545825668]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-10-07T10:19:51.125-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="2. Achieving rapid proof of concept to move a drug candidate through the pipeline quicker "
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h5"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-10-07T10:20:05.324-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>An important early step in the clinical trial process is to determine if the drug candidate achieves what it’s meant to. This is called a Proof of Concept (PoC) study. A PoC study is the first trial designed to evaluate how effective a drug is in treating people with the disease being studied. Getting to proof of concept more quickly allows AbbVie and other pharmaceutical companies to determine whether to progress a drug further in the clinical trial process.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <separator_copy_38965
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756423318]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-09-13T12:27:39.956-04:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-09-13T12:27:39.956-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <title2_copy_1760356570
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545824678,1651545825668]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-10-07T10:20:44.674-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="3. Selecting the best study sites to significantly increase productivity"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h5"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2_copy_210316413
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-10-07T10:21:00.098-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>Clinical trial sites are crucial to the drug development process. These sites provide a controlled, safe environment to test a drug candidate in patients through the help of site staff and investigators – doctors who are running each study in accordance with the sponsor’s (in this case, AbbVie’s) clinical trial design.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>AbbVie uses advanced analytics tools powered by artificial intelligence and machine learning to tap into decades of data to predict which clinical sites will get up and running quickly. This advanced technology is then layered with the historical knowledge and expertise of AbbVie’s medical directors, medical science liaisons and in-country leaders, who are experts in clinical site processes and work closely with the global healthcare providers who are the clinical trial investigators.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“We’re searching for sites that are knowledgeable about our disease areas, have access to the right patients and who are focused on getting results,” says Mike Foley, vice president, clinical development operations, AbbVie. “We draw on Machine Learning intel that pulls from historical performance data across industry to help us identify the best site partners. This approach helps us activate sites sooner and get data faster.”&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <separator_copy_38965_1294311964
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756423318]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-09-13T12:27:39.956-04:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-09-13T12:27:39.956-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <title2_copy_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545824678,1651545825668]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-10-07T10:21:14.166-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="4. Starting up quickly and engaging sites globally"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h5"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2_copy_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-10-07T10:21:28.169-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>Once the clinical trial sites have been selected, starting up a clinical study requires educational resources. To support sites with trial setup and launch, AbbVie has built a global team of dedicated clinical trial experts, known as the Study Start-Up (SSU) organization, to provide in-depth knowledge of country regulations, clinical trial site operations and processes for getting up and running.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>&amp;nbsp;“By working more closely with site teams, we've been able to better understand their needs, solve issues quickly, and speed up our clinical trials,” says Foley.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <separator_copy_38965_238995845
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756423318]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-09-13T12:27:39.956-04:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-09-13T12:27:39.956-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <title2_copy_340880564
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545824678,1651545825668]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-10-07T10:21:55.155-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="5. Creating robust regulatory submissions"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h5"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2_copy_1527372584
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-10-07T10:22:09.505-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>Clinical trials provide insights into a drug candidate’s safety and efficacy profile, safe dose range and any side effects—with the goal of illustrating that it safely and effectively treats the disease or medical condition. With this rich information, AbbVie’s regulatory team analyzes data and eventually prepares a thorough submission to regulatory bodies like the U.S. FDA. The company has leveraged artificial intelligence and automated tools to advance this process, shortening the submission timeline by about one month on average while continuing to prioritize high quality.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“From what our scientists do in the lab every day to how we discover new medicines, we strive to make transformational improvements that will have a lasting impact on patients,” Donoghoe says. “Pioneering new approaches isn't easy, but it’s what we must to do advance our mission because patients can’t wait.”&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4_copy>
                            <container4_copy_copy_264801824
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <text_copy
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-06-12T19:38:18.115-04:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="SCHAFSM"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-06-12T19:41:00.043-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="SCHAFSM"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>&lt;span class=&quot;body-unica-20-reg&quot;>&lt;b>Media inquiries:&lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;br>&#xa;Email:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;mailto:abbviemediarelations@abbvie.com&quot;>abbviemediarelations@abbvie.com&lt;/a>&lt;/p>&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4_copy_copy_264801824>
